          "reasoning": "Cross-table key strategy: All foreign key references resolve via master_kunden.kundennummer (normalized kunden_ref, kd_nummer, kunden_kenner). Project joins use projekt_kennung. Opportunity joins use opp_kennung. Key normalization must be consistent across all 5 models — strip any leading/trailing whitespace and apply LOWER() if needed before joining.\n\nEnum mapping strategy: German source values map to English target enums with explicit CASE WHEN logic per table. NULL is used as fallback for unmapped values in all enum columns (Customer_Tier__c, Role__c, Preferred_Language__c, StageName, Project_Status__c).\n\nDate parsing: All date fields (zieldatum/go_live_datum/garantieende) use TO_DATE with format guessing. DD.MM.YYYY is assumed for European format; YYYYMMDD detected via regex. Output ISO 'YYYY-MM-DD' strings. NULL preferred over sentinel dates.\n\nAmount handling: Strip currency symbols ('EUR ', '€') and text prefixes from auftragswert. Detect European format (dot thousand-separator, comma decimal) by counting dots/commas. Remove dots first, swap comma to period, then cast to DOUBLE PRECISION.\n\nLegacy columns: Each Legacy_*__c populated directly from source natural key without transformation — used for audit and row-level verification only.\nThe Account model reads directly from master_kunden, normalizing the kundennummer key via TRIM() to serve as both Id and Legacy_Customer_ID__c. The Customer_Tier__c enum is mapped from German source values (GOLD/SILVER/BRONZE/PLATINUM) to English using an explicit CASE WHEN with LOWER normalization, falling back to NULL for unmapped entries. All other fields pass through directly from the source, and placeholder dates/constants are used for CreatedDate, LastModifiedDate, and IsDeleted as no source timestamps are available."
